    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Answer user questions automatically for Conversational AI (01464)\n\n**Pattern:** Chatbot Responder · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Chat\n\n## What it does\nAnswer user questions automatically for Conversational AI (01464). It responds live to chat messages.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual conversational ai is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWhen Chat Message Received → Answer from Knowledge Base → Grounded Answer Found? → Deliver Answer via Slack → Align Field Names → Stamp Processing Time → Send Summary to Slack\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to chatbot responder without manual effort\n- Anyone automating conversational ai in ai\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: Google AI API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; Qdrant URL + key; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "f010aeb2-3bc1-7593-f0ff-1d5400dd952b",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "e4577b87-f269-388e-3e93-637f01b8880e",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -260
      ],
      "id": "d073401b-c407-44dc-c85d-e4fda4d30505",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your conversational ai process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
